    "summary": {
      "value": "Place cards as Vanguard Cards."
    },
    "description": "<blockquote><p><strong>Requirements:</strong> you must have mastered the <strong>Ace of Cards</strong> Class.<br /></p></blockquote><p>When you discard cards due to the <strong>Magic Cards</strong> Skill, you may choose 1 of them and place it face down in front of you as a <strong>vanguard card</strong> instead of putting it into your discard pile. You may only do so if you have <strong>two or fewer vanguard cards</strong> in play.</p><p>When a source deals damage to you and/or one or more allies you can see, you may reveal one of your <strong>vanguard cards</strong> in play. If you do and that card is a <strong>joker</strong> or its <strong>suit</strong> matches the damage type dealt by that source, you and every ally you can see gain Resistance to that damage type until the end of the current turn; then, put the revealed <strong>vanguard card</strong> on top of your <strong>discard pile</strong>, and it stops being a <strong>vanguard card</strong>.</p><p>You may look at your <strong>vanguard cards</strong> at any time. At the end of each conflict, if you have one or more <strong>vanguard cards</strong> in play, shuffle them back into your deck.</p>",
